195
00:15:25,706 --> 00:15:28,156
A dog?

196
00:15:28,156 --> 00:15:30,781
I gave her our card.

197
00:15:32,160 --> 00:15:33,731
She won't come.

198
00:15:33,731 --> 00:15:35,831
Why not?

199
00:15:35,831 --> 00:15:38,506
She saw you and ran. Right?

200
00:15:40,356 --> 00:15:42,406
Well...

201
00:15:43,240 --> 00:15:47,260
If you want to put it that way, yeah.

202
00:15:48,056 --> 00:15:52,189
She looked like she wanted to say something, though.

203
00:15:54,331 --> 00:15:57,297
Come on, you try. Down you go.

204
00:15:57,297 --> 00:15:59,647
Arms up. Like this.

205
00:15:59,647 --> 00:16:02,106
Deep breaths. One, two.

206
00:16:02,106 --> 00:16:06,439
Wow, you're good! Perfect! Perfect!

207
00:16:08,914 --> 00:16:12,164
<i>[Children of the Night]</i>

208
00:16:19,910 --> 00:16:24,414
Sou, we should really label the spices.

209
00:16:24,414 --> 00:16:27,397
They all look the same.

210
00:16:29,740 --> 00:16:31,206
Sou?

211
00:16:31,206 --> 00:16:33,110
Huh?

212
00:16:33,110 --> 00:16:34,650
What?

213
00:16:35,223 --> 00:16:38,210
She won't come this late.

214
00:16:38,864 --> 00:16:41,022
She might, on the last train.

215
00:16:41,022 --> 00:16:42,806
It's 2:00 a.m.

216
00:16:42,806 --> 00:16:45,697
Taxi, then.

217
00:16:45,697 --> 00:16:47,830
She's not coming.

218
00:16:48,422 --> 00:16:50,274
Come on, give up.

219
00:16:50,274 --> 00:16:51,840
Okay?

220
00:16:56,274 --> 00:16:57,874
Fine.

